Dialogue: 2,0:02:56.16,0:03:02.08,Mushisode Title,,0,0,0,eptitle,{\an6\fad(2000,0)\blur0.6\pos(1248,109)}The Warbling Seashell
Dialogue: 5,0:03:26.97,0:03:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, are you collecting seashells too?
Dialogue: 5,0:03:31.95,0:03:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, here. You take it.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:34.53,0:03:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You live above the cliffs, don't you?
Dialogue: 5,0:03:37.02,0:03:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet it's really hard finding seashells there.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:39.71,0:03:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-Thank you.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:43.25,0:03:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? So you {\i1}can{\i0} talk.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:46.83,0:03:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, want to come with me to somewhere that has even more seashells?
Dialogue: 5,0:03:50.51,0:03:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,'Kay.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:53.29,0:03:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you know?
Dialogue: 5,0:03:54.48,0:03:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If you put your ear to a seashell, \Nyou can hear the waves.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:00.73,0:04:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, you're right!
Dialogue: 5,0:04:03.43,0:04:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,See you again sometime, okay?
Dialogue: 5,0:04:06.71,0:04:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 5,0:04:07.66,0:04:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's play again!
Dialogue: 5,0:04:26.03,0:04:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Mina.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:28.03,0:04:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Mina!
Dialogue: 5,0:04:31.60,0:04:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to the village{,} and trade these for some rice.{villagers are fine, but not the fishermen}
Dialogue: 5,0:04:34.25,0:04:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:37.19,0:04:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure you don't talk to the shore folk.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:41.11,0:04:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:52.33,0:04:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me. Do you have a minute?
Dialogue: 5,0:04:56.33,0:04:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's asking?
Dialogue: 5,0:04:58.17,0:04:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a mushi-shi who's passing through.{Just your friendly neighborhood mushi-shi.}{i approve}
Dialogue: 5,0:04:59.76,0:05:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Ginko.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:02.11,0:05:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The sea {around here }is showing signs of an impending disaster,
Dialogue: 5,0:05:04.95,0:05:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,so I thought I should alert the nearby village.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:08.37,0:05:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,An impending disaster?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:17.49,0:05:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No one's here.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:22.31,0:05:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Maybe I could take a small break.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:29.07,0:05:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:32.11,0:05:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This one's so pretty.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:35.59,0:05:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if I can hear the waves in this one too.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:44.62,0:05:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:46.05,0:05:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Birds{'} singing?{rip rice}
Dialogue: 5,0:05:56.00,0:05:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I say "impending disaster,"
Dialogue: 5,0:05:57.66,0:06:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm not exactly sure what the disaster will be.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:00.65,0:06:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can assure you that one {\i1}will{\i0} happen—and soon.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:04.85,0:06:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You should tell the other villagers to be prepared for it.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:10.39,0:06:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll protect my own family.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:13.53,0:06:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The villagers can worry about themselves.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:15.35,0:06:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They've got nothing to do with me.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:21.33,0:06:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Mina.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:23.59,0:06:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Mina!
Dialogue: 5,0:06:28.33,0:06:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:29.79,0:06:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You seem out of it.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:31.85,0:06:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:39.33,0:06:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want me to take you home?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:42.89,0:06:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Shima, you sure this girl can talk?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:46.36,0:06:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, she's not saying anything.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:48.43,0:06:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,She can!
Dialogue: 5,0:06:51.45,0:06:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:52.70,0:06:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going home!
Dialogue: 5,0:06:54.55,0:06:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you ever listen to me?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:59.05,0:07:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And of all people, why would you talk to {\i1}her{\i0}?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:02.33,0:07:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you never to speak to that girl again.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:10.79,0:07:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:11.90,0:07:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Spit it out.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:15.77,0:07:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear the "song of the seashell"?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:25.29,0:07:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Although it's called the song of the seashell, \Nthe song actually comes from a mushi living inside of it.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:31.51,0:07:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called Yadokaridori or Saezurigai, which means "Hermit-Crab Bird" or "Warbling Shell."{respectively}{Yadokaridori: Hermit-Crab Bird \N Saezurigai: Warbling Shell}
Dialogue: 5,0:07:35.99,0:07:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,While they normally spend their time \Neating seaweed and flying over the sea,
Dialogue: 5,0:07:40.99,0:07:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,they come ashore when they sense an impending disaster.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:44.27,0:07:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They then hide in seashells \Nand wait for the disaster to pass.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:51.19,0:07:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that faint voice you heard, \Nthey sing, calling their family to safety.{land, where it's safer}
Dialogue: 5,0:07:58.11,0:08:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But when a person puts one of their shells to their ears,
Dialogue: 5,0:08:00.67,0:08:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that person forgets how to speak.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:04.74,0:08:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there a cure?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:07.19,0:08:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:08.33,0:08:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as she hears others talk each day, \Nshe'll get her speech back.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:13.21,0:08:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:16.61,0:08:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This only happened because you didn't listen.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:19.27,0:08:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd better not do it again, ever.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:22.02,0:08:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, that's the long and short of it.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:24.51,0:08:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The bigger issue is the disaster I mentioned.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:27.27,0:08:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll alert the village myself,
Dialogue: 5,0:08:29.56,0:08:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but you guys should be careful too.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:38.15,0:08:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There'll be a disaster at sea?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:41.15,0:08:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:42.93,0:08:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, a tidal wave?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:44.40,0:08:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying there's going to be a big storm?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:46.97,0:08:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. There are records of both of those happening.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:50.06,0:08:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You should all try to prepare yourselves.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:52.59,0:08:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We're {\i1}always{\i0} prepared.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:55.73,0:09:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way of knowing what might happen at sea.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:01.07,0:09:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So we prepare ourselves in every possible way.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:03.92,0:09:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for the warning,
Dialogue: 5,0:09:05.52,0:09:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but there's nothing else to be done.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:08.27,0:09:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good, then.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:10.07,0:09:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, stay sharp tomorrow too!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:12.54,0:09:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:14.37,0:09:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,950)}He always tells us to stay sharp,
Dialogue: 5,0:09:17.29,0:09:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,but all we ever do is tend to the fish cages.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:22.71,0:09:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, I'm bored.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:24.85,0:09:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to go back to {\i1}diving{\i0} for fish, not farming them.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:27.20,0:09:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Mind your tongue.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:28.58,0:09:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The chief fisherman had good reason to change things.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:31.69,0:09:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,If the fish farm works out, he can make sure we're fed {\i1}and{\i0} safe.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:36.19,0:09:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That way, this village will never see another tragedy.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:39.75,0:09:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,A tragedy?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:42.45,0:09:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it, again?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:44.33,0:09:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm... I'd say it's been nearly ten years now.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:47.60,0:09:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the divers from the chief's ship was eaten by a shark.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:52.36,0:09:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't pull her out of the water in time, you see.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:56.27,0:09:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:58.15,0:09:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That was terrible.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:00.81,0:10:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The sea that day was stained red with her blood.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:03.62,0:10:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Shortly after that happened, the diver's husband quit and stopped fishing with us.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:08.08,0:10:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He and his daughter live by themselves near the cliffs.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:13.51,0:10:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't say I don't understand him, though.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:16.55,0:10:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The chief pulled up his own wife first, you see.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:21.61,0:10:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know... I would've done the same thing he did.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:26.55,0:10:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, indeed.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:29.11,0:10:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's when the chief had us try fish farming.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:34.15,0:10:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I can understand him as well.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:37.59,0:10:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a painful tragedy for everyone.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:47.93,0:10:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back, Dad.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:49.52,0:10:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:51.87,0:10:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So... today on the shore, I saw Mina.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:56.18,0:11:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But then Mina's dad said she's not allowed to talk to me.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:03.17,0:11:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder how come.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:07.11,0:11:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:10.70,0:11:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:12.97,0:11:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let that get to you.{it's a "don't let it bother you" kind of thing}
Dialogue: 5,0:11:16.89,0:11:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't do anything wrong.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:22.79,0:11:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, I understand.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:27.57,0:11:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:37.41,0:11:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch out!
Dialogue: 5,0:11:38.48,0:11:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a shark!
Dialogue: 5,0:11:41.97,0:11:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Your wife was...
Dialogue: 5,0:12:02.15,0:12:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If only I had been on that boat with her,
Dialogue: 5,0:12:03.90,0:12:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,this wouldn't have happened.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:06.43,0:12:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Sakichi, there was nothing anyone could have done.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:13.09,0:12:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,"Nothing"?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:15.23,0:12:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If you say so.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:17.37,0:12:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess it was my own fault for putting my wife's life in someone else's hands.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:21.65,0:12:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Please get out.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:25.05,0:12:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}From now on, I'll protect my own family.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:00.67,0:13:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Even more of them have come ashore.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:05.97,0:13:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In that faint voice, the seashells are crying out...
Dialogue: 5,0:13:10.27,0:13:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}for the sake of their family...
Dialogue: 5,0:13:12.61,0:13:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and themselves.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:40.15,0:13:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That girl's something else.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:42.87,0:13:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,She's still so little.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:44.57,0:13:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:47.43,0:13:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,She's been diving in place of her mom all this time.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:52.13,0:13:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't help but feel sorry for her.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:06.83,0:14:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm? What is it?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:13.39,0:14:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You must never tell anyone else about this.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:16.75,0:14:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if something happens to me,
Dialogue: 5,0:14:19.95,0:14:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,with this, you'll be able to get by.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:24.71,0:14:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,No one else is going to protect you.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:30.45,0:14:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have to protect yourself, first and foremost.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:39.09,0:14:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's there?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:42.05,0:14:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's me.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:43.63,0:14:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I came to talk to you.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:48.59,0:14:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,A mushi-shi came to tell us that a disaster at sea will soon happen.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:52.98,0:14:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You two should be careful too.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:57.07,0:14:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the last person I want to hear that from.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:00.77,0:15:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 5,0:15:01.99,0:15:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,don't you have any idea what's going to happen?
Dialogue: 5,0:15:05.65,0:15:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You were always the first to sense when something was wrong with the sea.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:11.57,0:15:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I care.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:13.67,0:15:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Sakichi, for the last ten years,
Dialogue: 5,0:15:18.08,0:15:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,this village has managed to avoid any other accidents.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:21.78,0:15:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not about to let anyone die on my watch again.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:28.63,0:15:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So could you please come back to the village and help with the fish farm?
Dialogue: 5,0:15:32.79,0:15:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We've finally managed to make the fish farm sustainable.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:38.33,0:15:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, everyone can feed themselves without having to worry.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:42.87,0:15:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you and your little girl keep on fishing alone, you two may run into danger someday.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:48.31,0:15:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that really what you want?
Dialogue: 5,0:15:51.93,0:15:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew you for a long time.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:53.83,0:15:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I know there's probably someone you blame more than me.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:57.43,0:16:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can't go on blaming yourself anymore! You have to stop.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:01.68,0:16:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You have something more important to worry about.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:04.93,0:16:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you care about your daughter's future, so please...
Dialogue: 5,0:16:07.91,0:16:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,come back.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:16.57,0:16:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll come again.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:18.59,0:16:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then, please be careful.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:38.89,0:16:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The singing stopped.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:49.37,0:16:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:50.76,0:16:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Just in case, I'll have everyone take refuge on top of the cliffs.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:10.81,0:17:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw something!
Dialogue: 5,0:17:13.15,0:17:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at them...
Dialogue: 5,0:17:14.62,0:17:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So many dead fish.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:16.77,0:17:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 5,0:17:25.31,0:17:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a red tide!{obv. they're all remakes}
Dialogue: 5,0:17:50.03,0:17:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,How could this... happen?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:55.99,0:18:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how we run, we can't escape tragedy.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:03.51,0:18:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, there really {\i1}was{\i0}...
Dialogue: 5,0:18:08.48,0:18:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing we could've done.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:17.77,0:18:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,There was nothing anyone could have done.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:30.65,0:18:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The red tide's finally retreating, huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:18:34.47,0:18:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:36.23,0:18:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess this marks the end of the fish farm.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:39.20,0:18:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Nah, we can dive for some more and start over again.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:42.42,0:18:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:47.44,0:18:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So you still don't have your voice back?
Dialogue: 5,0:18:50.71,0:18:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 5,0:18:52.89,0:18:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It might be better to let her hear more voices.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:59.99,0:19:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I'm off again.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:14.83,0:19:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's strange.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:16.23,0:19:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Although the red tide has receded, they haven't returned to sea yet.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:22.15,0:19:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Does that mean...
Dialogue: 5,0:19:24.79,0:19:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the disaster isn't over yet?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:30.97,0:19:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Mina.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:33.75,0:19:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Come with me.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:43.21,0:19:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Sakichi!
Dialogue: 5,0:19:45.47,0:19:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't go diving yet.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:47.67,0:19:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,After a red tide, shellfish may become poisonous.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:51.43,0:19:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That only happens rarely.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:53.49,0:19:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You should know that.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:55.74,0:19:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We have no other choice.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:59.77,0:20:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think you should either.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:03.41,0:20:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The omen hasn't yet passed.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:06.81,0:20:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Then... what are we supposed to do?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:10.57,0:20:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh, Sakichi?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:12.16,0:20:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you suggest we all get by until we can live off the sea again?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:22.85,0:20:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Open it.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:31.27,0:20:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Mina found that pearl.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:33.57,0:20:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We can sell it and share the money.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:35.76,0:20:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't be a whole lot, but it should be enough.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:38.43,0:20:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But to give us something so precious...
Dialogue: 5,0:20:41.65,0:20:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's better than letting someone else die, isn't it?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:44.93,0:20:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But in exchange,
Dialogue: 5,0:20:47.05,0:20:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,please let me and my daughter come back to the village.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:01.95,0:21:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 5,0:21:04.15,0:21:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course we will!
Dialogue: 5,0:21:08.67,0:21:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Later on, along nearby shores, the villagers found a few dead seabirds, probably from eating poisonous shellfish.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:17.61,0:21:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}However, no one from that particular village died.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:43.39,0:21:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Mina!
Dialogue: 5,0:21:45.77,0:21:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on!
Dialogue: 5,0:21:47.46,0:21:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Coming!
Dialogue: 5,0:21:51.69,0:21:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What were you staring at?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:53.08,0:21:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:54.20,0:21:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, nothing.
